Sure! Here's a JavaScript function that generates a random integer between two specified integers:

```javascript
function getRandomInteger(min, max) {
  return Math.floor(Math.random() * (max - min + 1)) + min;
}
```

You can use this function by passing the minimum and maximum values as arguments. For example, `getRandomInteger(1, 10)` will return a random integer between 1 and 10 (inclusive).
